properties.abstract: Those who know the Schilt area from ski or snowshoe tours could be  surprised by the terrain’s colours in summer: from Rotärd (red earth) to Wisschamm (white ridge), Schwarzstöckli (black peak) and Gufelstock the ground is red, green, white and finally black. The itinerary touches six low summits. A network of hiking trails offer a multitude of variants to shorten or extend this tour. Therefore, it is ideal for those who travel by public transport.
properties.subtitle: Colourful hustle and bustle above the "Zigerschlitz"
properties.title: Fronalp - Schwarzstöckli - Gufelstock - Bärenboden

sac_photos.title: On Gufelstock: view back to the summits traversed on the way
Red earth at Rotärd; behind are Tödi, Clariden and Glärnisch.

segments.description: From Naturfreundehaus Fronalp ascend on the marked mountain hiking trail to reach Fronalppass via Mittelstafel and Ober Stafel. Continue southward past Färistock to reach the foot of Siwellen. Now bypass this elevation on the left (east) to the saddle called Rotärd. Continue via Wisschamm and Schwarzstöckli to P. 2313.
segments.title: Fronalp Naturfreundehaus - Rotärd - col Schwarzstöckli/Heustock P. 2313

segments.description: Ascend pathless and southward to Heustock. Now follow the faint path (white-blue markings) on the ridge via Chli Höch and Höch to Gufelstock. Several small towers on this ridge are either traversed or bypassed (easier).

photos.caption: The passage of the Höch summits on the way to Gufelstock

segments.title: P. 2313 Heustock - Gufelstock

segments.description: From Gufelstock descend on the white-red mountain hiking trail to reach the small fabled lakes on Alp Fesis. At 2060 m a marked mountain hiking trail traverses up and down westward to reach a saddle (P. 1972) at Schafleger. From there a steep, but well-marked descent leads to the aerial cableway at Bärenboden with its summit station a few minutes after Äugstenhütte (food an beverage).
segments.title: Gufelstock - Fesis - Äugsten/Bärenboden
